    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-06-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-06-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 11, 1890</date>. (Received June
                            24.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 93.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 55, dated the 3d ultimo,
                        relating to the case of Nicolino Mileo, was duly received.</p>
                <p>I have not yet submitted the case to the minister for foreign affairs, having
                        had a desire, before doing so, to give a more careful study to the questions
                        which it involves.</p>
                <p>I expect to present Mileo’s case the first of next week, when the minister
                        will receive the members of the diplomatic corps. I shall first submit a
                        note and shall then ask that a special audience shall as soon afterwards as
                        practicable be given to me with regard to the case and with a view, also, of
                        urging the adoption of amendments to our treaties with Italy in relation to
                        the subjects of naturalization and the extradition of offenders.</p>
                <p>I have, etc,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. G. Porter.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
